race.comment: ALABAMA FOX (6) returns from a 20-week spell. Wasn't disgraced in a couple of Group 3 races last prep after making her mark with consecutive wins at the provincials. This is not a strong race so on the back of two trials she should be forward enough to run a big race. MAMUSHKA (9) ran on well but was no match for the in-form scratched JELLICIOUS over 1200m at Warwick Farm last time out. Fitter for two runs back from a spell and on current form is the measuring stick. FLEETING SPIRIT (7) also made late ground in the JELLICIOUS race recently, clocking in just under a length behind MAMUSHKA. Beaten a neck in a similar race to this under this weight at the same stage of last prep. Major player. MASTER OF DISGUISE (5) did enough first-up in a Randwick Highway to suggest she has come back in good order. Will appreciate a step up in trip today so keep her in mind. SCALABLE (11) is trialling well and looks set for a decent return from a 33-week break.
